### The ISO 26262 Framework

**ISO 26262** is the international standard for functional safety in road vehicles. It defines requirements across the entire safety lifecycle for **ASIL (Automotive Safety Integrity Levels)** , from A (lowest) to D (highest).

| **ASIL Level** | **Application** | **Requirement** |
|---|---|---|
| **ASIL A** | Minor safety functions | Basic process compliance |
| **ASIL B** | Moderate safety functions | Systematic and random fault mitigation |
| **ASIL C** | High safety functions | Rigorous verification and validation |
| **ASIL D** | **Critical safety functions** | Maximum rigor — braking, steering, airbags |

**ST-T1024 is designed to meet ASIL B/C/D requirements by construction.**

